wikipedia_page.main: Frederick Francis Finch (1830 – 5 May 1892) was an English cricketer who made one first-class cricket appearance for Kent County Cricket Club in 1862. He was christened at East Grinstead in Sussex on 12 December 1830.Finch made his only first-class appearance for Kent against Yorkshire at Cranbrook in July 1862. He worked as a veterinarian. He married Amelia Southon on 11 May 1852 and the couple had nine children. He died at Sevenoaks in Kent in May 1892 aged 62.
